    <article id=3D"main-content" class=3D"article">
      <header class=3D"article-header">
        <h1 title=3D"Launch Control XL 3 programmer's DAW mode" class=3D"ar=
ticle-title">
          Launch Control XL 3 programmer's DAW mode
         =20
        </h1>

        <div class=3D"article-author">
         =20
          <div class=3D"article-meta">
           =20

            <div class=3D"meta-group">
             =20
                <span class=3D"meta-data"><time datetime=3D"2025-07-07T14:0=
6:15Z" title=3D"07/07/2025, 17:06" data-datetime=3D"relative">6 months ago<=
/time></span>
                <span class=3D"meta-data">Updated</span>
             =20
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

       =20
      </header>

      <section class=3D"article-info">
        <div class=3D"article-content">
          <div class=3D"article-body"><div lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr" class=3D=
"section top-level-topic zd-article section" xml:lang=3D"en">
<p>DAW mode provides additional functionality, allowing DAWs and DAW-like s=
oftware to realise intuitive user interfaces on the <span class=3D"phrase">=
Launch Control XL 3</span>=E2=80=99s surface. The capabilities described in=
 this chapter are only available once DAW mode is enabled.</p>
<p>All functionality described in this chapter is accessible through the DA=
W In/Out (USB) interface.&nbsp;</p>
<div dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"note" style=3D"margin-left: 0.5in; margin-right: =
0.5in;">
<h3 class=3D"title">Note</h3>
<p>MIDI data is not sent from the DIN outputs in this mode.</p>
</div>
<div xml:lang=3D"en" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"section sub-topic">
<div class=3D"titlepage">
<h2 class=3D"title">
<a data-zd-article=3D"UUID-844dc51d-841a-efdb-0f22-d4d952cf327a" id=3D"UUID=
-e854bf5b-4e86-1ad4-74dc-e052793075fb"></a>DAW mode control</h2>
</div>
<p>You can enabling and disabling DAW Mode using either a note, or SysEx me=
ssage:</p>
<p>Enable DAW Mode:</p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Hex: &nbsp; &nbsp; 9fh &nbsp; &nbsp;0Ch &nbsp; &nbs=
p;7Fh</code></p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Dec: &nbsp; &nbsp; 159 &nbsp; &nbsp;12 &nbsp; &nbsp=
; 127</code></p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Hex: &nbsp; &nbsp; F0h 00h 20h 29h 02h 15h 02h 7Fh =
F7h</code></p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Dec: &nbsp; &nbsp; 240 0 &nbsp; 32 &nbsp;41 &nbsp;2=
 &nbsp; 21 &nbsp;2 &nbsp; 127 247</code></p>
<p>Disable DAW Mode:</p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Hex: &nbsp; &nbsp; 9Fh &nbsp; &nbsp;0Ch &nbsp; &nbs=
p;00h</code></p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Dec: &nbsp; &nbsp; 159 &nbsp; &nbsp;12 &nbsp; &nbsp=
; 0</code></p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Hex: &nbsp; &nbsp; F0h 00h 20h 29h 02h 15h 02h 00h =
F7h</code></p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Dec: &nbsp; &nbsp; 240 0 &nbsp; 32 &nbsp;41 &nbsp;2=
 &nbsp; 21 &nbsp;2 &nbsp; 0 &nbsp; 247</code></p>
<p>Once the DAW or DAW-like software has recognised and connected to the <s=
pan class=3D"phrase">Launch Control XL 3</span>, it should tell the <span c=
lass=3D"phrase">Launch Control XL 3</span> to enter DAW mode (send either o=
f the =E2=80=98Enable DAW Mode=E2=80=99 messages above), and then, if neces=
sary, enable the feature controls (see the <span class=3D"phrase">Launch Co=
ntrol XL 3</span> <a class=3D"link linktype-component" href=3D"https://user=
guides.novationmusic.com/hc/en-gb/articles/27840466607890#UUID-8a0094d1-308=
5-4f52-327a-642c298296dd" title=3D"Launch Control XL 3 feature Controls">fe=
ature controls</a> section of this document).</p>
<p>When the DAW or DAW-like software exits, it should exit from DAW mode on=
 the <span class=3D"phrase">Launch Control XL 3</span> (send either of the =
=E2=80=98Disable DAW Mode=E2=80=99 messages above), to return it to Standal=
one (MIDI) mode.</p>
<div xml:lang=3D"en" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"section sub-topic">
<div class=3D"titlepage">
<h3 class=3D"title">
<a data-zd-article=3D"UUID-844dc51d-841a-efdb-0f22-d4d952cf327a" id=3D"UUID=
-4e9989a9-09e2-a755-05e6-119003624052"></a>The surface in DAW mode</h3>
</div>
<p>In DAW mode, contrary to standalone (MIDI) mode, all buttons, and surfac=
e elements not belonging to performance features (such as the Custom Modes)=
 can be accessed and will report on the DAW In/Out (USB) interface only. Th=
e controls are mapped to Control Change events as follows:</p>
<div class=3D"mediaobject">
<table class=3D"image-viewport" summary=3D"manufactured viewport for HTML i=
mg" style=3D"border-collapse:collapse;border:0; width:50%;">
<tbody><tr>
<td style=3D"padding:0;"><a data-lightbox=3D"lightbox-images" href=3D"https=
://userguides.novationmusic.com/hc/article_attachments/27840434038546"><img=
 src=3D"https://userguides.novationmusic.com/hc/article_attachments/2784043=
4038546" style=3D"width: 100%;" alt=3D"LCXL3_Programmer_s_DAW_Mode_CCs_deci=
mal.png"></a></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<div class=3D"caption">
<p>Decimal values</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"mediaobject">
<table class=3D"image-viewport" summary=3D"manufactured viewport for HTML i=
mg" style=3D"border-collapse:collapse;border:0; width:50%;">
<tbody><tr>
<td style=3D"padding:0;"><a data-lightbox=3D"lightbox-images" href=3D"https=
://userguides.novationmusic.com/hc/article_attachments/27840445891986"><img=
 src=3D"https://userguides.novationmusic.com/hc/article_attachments/2784044=
5891986" style=3D"width: 100%;" alt=3D"LCXL3_Programmer_s_DAW_Mode_CCs_hexa=
decimal.png"></a></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<div class=3D"caption">
<p>Hexadecimal values</p>
</div>
</div>
<p>Encoders and faders output on channel 16, the buttons output on channel =
1 except shift which outputs on on channel 7 as this is linked to its <a cl=
ass=3D"link linktype-component" href=3D"https://userguides.novationmusic.co=
m/hc/en-gb/articles/27840466607890#UUID-8a0094d1-3085-4f52-327a-642c298296d=
d" title=3D"Launch Control XL 3 feature Controls">feature control</a>.</p>
<p>The Control Change indices listed are also used for sending colour to th=
e corresponding LEDs, see <a class=3D"xref linktype-component" href=3D"http=
s://userguides.novationmusic.com/hc/en-gb/articles/27840466544402-Launch-Co=
ntrol-XL-3-programmer-s-DAW-mode#UUID-08b8f2ea-88aa-1622-c3c6-39da863c722f"=
 title=3D"Colouring the surface">Colouring the surface</a>.</p>
<div class=3D"glossary-definitions" style=3D"display:none!important;"></div=
>
</div>
<div xml:lang=3D"en" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"section sub-topic">
<div class=3D"titlepage">
<h3 class=3D"title">
<a data-zd-article=3D"UUID-844dc51d-841a-efdb-0f22-d4d952cf327a" id=3D"UUID=
-ffbf3a18-f903-3758-5a75-8f228ce5aa7d"></a>Additional modes available in DA=
W mode</h3>
</div>
<p>Once in DAW mode, the following additional modes become available:</p>
<div class=3D"itemizedlist">
<ul class=3D"itemizedlist" style=3D"list-style-type: disc;">
<li class=3D"listitem">
<p>DAW Control Mode</p>
</li>
<li class=3D"listitem">
<p>DAW Mixer Mode</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class=3D"glossary-definitions" style=3D"display:none!important;"></div=
>
</div>
<div xml:lang=3D"en" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"section sub-topic">
<div class=3D"titlepage">
<h3 class=3D"title">
<a data-zd-article=3D"UUID-844dc51d-841a-efdb-0f22-d4d952cf327a" id=3D"UUID=
-66332331-3497-21a7-45bb-612133d2fc07"></a>Mode report and select</h3>
</div>
<p>The surface mode can be controlled by MIDI events and are reported back =
by the <span class=3D"phrase">Launch Control XL 3</span> whenever it change=
s mode due to user activity. These messages are important to capture, as th=
e DAW should follow them when setting up and using the surfaces as intended=
 based on the selected mode.</p>
<p>Mode changes are reported or can be changed by the following MIDI event:=
</p>
<div class=3D"itemizedlist">
<ul class=3D"itemizedlist" style=3D"list-style-type: disc;">
<li class=3D"listitem">
<p>Channel 7 (MIDI status: B6h, 182), Control Change 1Eh (30)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<p>The modes are mapped to the following values:</p>
<div class=3D"itemizedlist">
<ul class=3D"itemizedlist" style=3D"list-style-type: disc;">
<li class=3D"listitem">
<p>01h (1): DAW Mixer</p>
</li>
<li class=3D"listitem">
<p>02h (2): DAW Control</p>
</li>
<li class=3D"listitem">
<p>06h-09h(6-9): Custom Modes 1 - 4</p>
</li>
<li class=3D"listitem">
<p>12h-1dh(18-29): Custom Modes 5-16</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class=3D"glossary-definitions" style=3D"display:none!important;"></div=
>
</div>
<div xml:lang=3D"en" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"section sub-topic">
<div class=3D"titlepage">
<h3 class=3D"title">
<a data-zd-article=3D"UUID-844dc51d-841a-efdb-0f22-d4d952cf327a" id=3D"UUID=
-b0ac8673-b77a-f2d5-c87c-0818a25e063f"></a>Absolute and relative encoder mo=
des</h3>
</div>
<p>By default encoders are in absolute mode and provide standard CCs as des=
cribed above. If the DAW sends them position information, they automaticall=
y pick that up.</p>
<p>Each row can be independently switched into relative mode</p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Hex: &nbsp; &nbsp;B6h &lt;RowID&gt; &lt;7Fh:On/00h:=
Off&gt;</code></p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Dec: &nbsp; &nbsp;182 &lt;RowID&gt; &lt;127:On/0:Of=
f&gt;</code></p>
<div class=3D"itemizedlist">
<ul class=3D"itemizedlist" style=3D"list-style-type: disc;">
<li class=3D"listitem">
<p>45h (69): Row 1</p>
</li>
<li class=3D"listitem">
<p>48h (72): Row 2</p>
</li>
<li class=3D"listitem">
<p>49h (73): Row 3</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<p>In Relative mode, the pivot value is 40h(64) (no movement). Values above=
 the pivot point encode clockwise movements. Values below the pivot point e=
ncode anticlockwise movements. For example, 41h(65) corresponds to 1 step c=
lockwise and 3Fh(63) corresponds to 1 step anticlockwise.</p>
<p>When in relative mode, the CC numbers increase by 40h(64) for each row o=
f encoders:</p>
<p>Row 1: 4dh (77) - 54h (84)&nbsp;</p>
<p>Row 2: 55h (85) - 5ch (92)</p>
<p>Row 3: 5dh (93) - 64h (100)</p>
<div class=3D"glossary-definitions" style=3D"display:none!important;"></div=
>
</div>
<div xml:lang=3D"en" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"section sub-topic">
<div class=3D"titlepage">
<h3 class=3D"title">
<a data-zd-article=3D"UUID-844dc51d-841a-efdb-0f22-d4d952cf327a" id=3D"UUID=
-5154800e-17f1-6377-45bf-4180051ea8e1"></a>Continuous control touch events<=
/h3>
</div>
<p><code class=3D"code">Hex: &nbsp; &nbsp;B6h 47h &lt;7Fh:On/00h:Off&gt;</c=
ode></p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Dec: &nbsp; &nbsp;182 71 &lt;127:On/0:Off&gt;</code=
></p>
<p>If Continuous Control Touch events are enabled, the Touch On is sent as =
a Control Change event with Value 127 on Channel 15, while the Touch Off is=
 sent as a Control Change event with Value 0 on Channel 15. For example, th=
e leftmost Fader would send <span class=3D"bold"><strong>BEh 05h 7Fh</stron=
g></span> (190 5 127) for Touch On, and <span class=3D"bold"><strong>BEh 05=
h 00h</strong></span> (190 5 0) for Touch Off.</p>
<div class=3D"glossary-definitions" style=3D"display:none!important;"></div=
>
</div>
<div class=3D"glossary-definitions" style=3D"display:none!important;"></div=
>
</div>
<div xml:lang=3D"en" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"section sub-topic">
<div class=3D"titlepage">
<h2 class=3D"title">
<a data-zd-article=3D"UUID-844dc51d-841a-efdb-0f22-d4d952cf327a" id=3D"UUID=
-08b8f2ea-88aa-1622-c3c6-39da863c722f"></a>Colouring the surface</h2>
</div>
<p>For all controls, or a control change matching those described in the re=
ports can be sent to colour the corresponding LED (if the control has any).=
</p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Hex: &nbsp; &nbsp;B0h &lt;control index&gt; &lt;col=
our index&gt;</code></p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Dec: &nbsp; &nbsp;176 &lt;control index&gt; &lt;col=
our index&gt;</code></p>
<div dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"note" style=3D"margin-left: 0.5in; margin-right: =
0.5in;">
<h3 class=3D"title">Note</h3>
<p>The Shift button is excluded as it is tied to a Feature Control message.=
 See <a class=3D"xref linktype-component" href=3D"https://userguides.novati=
onmusic.com/hc/en-gb/articles/27840466607890#UUID-8a0094d1-3085-4f52-327a-6=
42c298296dd" title=3D"Launch Control XL 3 feature Controls"><span class=3D"=
phrase">Launch Control XL 3</span> feature Controls</a> section for further=
 information.</p>
</div>
<div xml:lang=3D"en" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"section sub-topic">
<div class=3D"titlepage">
<h3 class=3D"title">
<a data-zd-article=3D"UUID-844dc51d-841a-efdb-0f22-d4d952cf327a" id=3D"UUID=
-89e3673e-e6b6-ac79-e5ff-1f95cc4ce7c0"></a>RGB Colour</h3>
</div>
<p>Buttons and encoder LEDs can also be set to a custom colour using the fo=
llowing SysEx:</p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Hex: &nbsp; &nbsp;F0h 00h 20h 29h 02h 15h 01h 53h &=
lt;control index&gt; &lt;R&gt; &lt;G&gt; &lt;B&gt; F7h</code></p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Dec: &nbsp; &nbsp;240 0 &nbsp; 32 &nbsp;41 &nbsp;2 =
&nbsp; 21 &nbsp;1 &nbsp; 83 &nbsp;&lt;control index&gt; &lt;R&gt; &lt;G&gt;=
 &lt;B&gt; 247</code></p>
<p>Encoder LEDs can be addressed using the absolute mode control indices wh=
en encoders are in either absolute or relative mode.&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"glossary-definitions" style=3D"display:none!important;"></div=
>
</div>
<div xml:lang=3D"en" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"section sub-topic">
<div class=3D"titlepage">
<h3 class=3D"title">
<a data-zd-article=3D"UUID-844dc51d-841a-efdb-0f22-d4d952cf327a" id=3D"UUID=
-bb3e8360-5d8a-c02a-48da-c82e5536671a"></a>Colour palette</h3>
</div>
<p>When providing colours by MIDI notes or control changes, the colours are=
 chosen according to the following table, decimal:</p>
