<div dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"note" style=3D"margin-left: 0.5in; margin-right: =
0.5in;">
<h3 class=3D"title">Note</h3>
<p>The arrangement is ignored for targets only setting names (22h(34) =E2=
=80=93 28h(40)), however for changing triggerability, it needs to be set no=
n-zero (since the value 0 for these still acts for cancelling the display).=
</p>
</div>
<div class=3D"glossary-definitions" style=3D"display:none!important;"></div=
>
</div>
<div class=3D"glossary-definitions" style=3D"display:none!important;"></div=
>
</div>
<div xml:lang=3D"en" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"section sub-topic">
<div class=3D"titlepage">
<h3 class=3D"title">
<a data-zd-article=3D"UUID-844dc51d-841a-efdb-0f22-d4d952cf327a" id=3D"UUID=
-16a5792a-5ffc-d80b-b397-5050d155331a"></a>Setting text</h3>
</div>
<p>Once a display is configured, the following message can be used to fill =
in the text fields.</p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Hex: &nbsp; &nbsp;F0h 00h 20h 29h 02h 15h 06h &lt;t=
arget&gt; &lt;field&gt; &lt;text=E2=80=A6&gt; F7h</code></p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Dec: &nbsp; &nbsp;240 0 &nbsp; 32 &nbsp;41 &nbsp;2 =
&nbsp; 21 &nbsp;6 &nbsp; &lt;target&gt; &lt;field&gt; &lt;text=E2=80=A6&gt;=
 247</code></p>
<p>The text uses the standard ASCII character mapping in the range 20h (32)=
 =E2=80=93 7Eh (126) with the addition of the below control codes, which ha=
ve been reassigned to provide additional non-ASCII characters.</p>
<div class=3D"itemizedlist">
<ul class=3D"itemizedlist" style=3D"list-style-type: disc;">
<li class=3D"listitem">
<p>Empty Box - 1Bh (27)</p>
</li>
<li class=3D"listitem">
<p>Filled Box - 1Ch (28)</p>
</li>
<li class=3D"listitem">
<p>Flat Symbol - 1Dh (29)</p>
</li>
<li class=3D"listitem">
<p>Heart - 1Eh (30)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<p>Other control characters should not be used as their behaviour may chang=
e in the future.</p>
<div class=3D"glossary-definitions" style=3D"display:none!important;"></div=
>
</div>
<div xml:lang=3D"en" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"section sub-topic">
<div class=3D"titlepage">
<h3 class=3D"title">
<a data-zd-article=3D"UUID-844dc51d-841a-efdb-0f22-d4d952cf327a" id=3D"UUID=
-35d7c411-632e-3bcc-c23d-c1b243c6287d"></a>Bitmap</h3>
</div>
<p>The screen can also display custom graphics by sending a bitmap to the d=
evice.</p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Hex: &nbsp; &nbsp;F0h 00h 20h 29h 02h 15h 09h &lt;t=
arget&gt; &lt;bitmap_data&gt; 7Fh</code></p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Dec: &nbsp; &nbsp;240 0 &nbsp; 32 &nbsp;41 &nbsp;2 =
&nbsp; 21 &nbsp;9 &nbsp; &lt;target&gt; &lt;bitmap_data&gt; 127</code></p>
<p>The &lt;target&gt; can be either the Stationary display (20h(32)) or the=
 Global temporary display (21h(33)). There is no effect on other targets.</=
p>
<p>The &lt;bitmap_data&gt; is of fixed 1216 bytes, 19 bytes for each pixel =
row, for a total of 64 rows (19 =C3=97 64 =3D 1216). The 7 bits of the SysE=
x byte encode pixels from left to right (highest bit corresponding to the l=
eftmost pixel), the 19 bytes covering the 128 pixels width of the display (=
with five unused bits in the last byte).</p>
<p>Upon success, there is a response to this message, which is suitable for=
 timing fluid animations (once receiving it, the <span class=3D"phrase">Lau=
nch Control XL 3</span> is ready to accept a next Bitmap message):</p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Hex: &nbsp; &nbsp;F0h 00h 20h 29h 02h 15h 09h 7Fh</=
code></p>
<p><code class=3D"code">Dec: &nbsp; &nbsp;240 0 &nbsp; 32 &nbsp;41 &nbsp;2 =
&nbsp; 21 &nbsp;9 &nbsp; 127</code></p>
<p>The display can be cancelled by either cancelling it explicitly (using t=
he Configure Display SysEx or MIDI Event), or triggering the normal display=
 (whose parameters are preserved while the bitmap is displaying).</p>
<div dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"important" style=3D"margin-left: 0.5in; margin-ri=
ght: 0.5in;">
<h3 class=3D"title">Important</h3>
<p>The firmware can only hold one bitmap in its memory at once.</p>
</div>
<div class=3D"glossary-definitions" style=3D"display:none!important;"></div=
>
</div>
<div class=3D"glossary-definitions" style=3D"display:none!important;"></div=
>
</div>
<div class=3D"glossary-definitions" style=3D"display:none!important;"></div=
>
</div>
</div>

